-- Perrigo Advances to Record High, Closes Gap With U.S. Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-06-17T09:02:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-17/perrigo-advances-to-record-high-closes-gap-with-u-s-shares.html
Perrigo Co. (PRGO) , the largest U.S.
generic over-the-counter maker of drugs, advanced to the highest
on record in  Tel Aviv , closing the gap with its U.S. traded
shares.  The  shares  gained 3 percent to 432.7 shekels, or the
equivalent of $112.28, at 11:37 a.m. in Tel Aviv, the highest
level since March 2005, when the shares were listed in Tel Aviv.
The U.S. traded shares advanced 1.1 percent to $111.62 on June
15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
